1
00:00:00,120 --> 00:00:02,680
They took me to the Investigation Section and up to the second floor

2
00:00:05,519 --> 00:00:10,240
They brought me into a room on the second floor, where the Investigation Section was located

3
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:15,679
It was headed by Abu Hamza al-Tunisi, the senior <i>sharia</i> official and overall emir

4
00:00:15,679 --> 00:00:18,839
Under him were the Emir of Investigation, Abu Seif Maqs, and Abu Hudhayfa

5
00:00:19,359 --> 00:00:22,120
And Abu Zaid, from the Sakhani clan

6
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:25,239
His brother, Fayez, was the Emir of the Islamic Police

7
00:00:25,280 --> 00:00:26,719
They took me upstairs

8
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:29,480
My hands were tied behind my back

9
00:00:30,079 --> 00:00:32,679
And I was blindfolded, and they began beating me

10
00:00:32,719 --> 00:00:36,719
They hit me with sticks and metal rods , the beating was extremely painful

11
00:00:37,880 --> 00:00:41,880
I was beaten for 3 days straight

12
00:00:42,679 --> 00:00:46,359
They poured water on me and kept beating me again and again

13
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:51,799
When I woke up, I found myself hanging on the wall on the second floor

14
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:58,200
That area was at the start of Sajiyah Street, at the intersection with Hittin School Street

15
00:00:59,799 --> 00:01:02,200
That place was known as the Investigation Zone

16
00:01:02,280 --> 00:01:03,679
I found myself hanging

17
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:07,200
I remained hanging on the wall for 18 days

18
00:01:08,719 --> 00:01:12,120
It was the middle of the hot summer season

19
00:01:12,640 --> 00:01:16,040
But our Lord, praise be to Him, is merciful in His mercy

20
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:17,920
And in His glory and majesty

21
00:01:18,400 --> 00:01:21,319
The heat actually helped me endure the beatings and pain

22
00:01:21,359 --> 00:01:26,480
When my body was hot and sweating, the blows hurt less than when it was cold in winter

23
00:01:29,359 --> 00:01:31,480
I suffered terribly from thirst

24
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:34,560
My toes barely touched the ground

25
00:01:34,599 --> 00:01:38,400
And I could hardly reach a bottle of drink

26
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:41,920
I would bring it close when they gave me a break to drink, from the intensity of thirst

27
00:01:41,959 --> 00:01:43,239
Because of the severe torture

28
00:01:44,079 --> 00:01:46,439
Abu Seif wrapped his hand around my beard

29
00:01:47,439 --> 00:01:51,760
He grabbed my beard,it was long,and dragged me by it while my hands were shackled

30
00:01:51,959 --> 00:01:56,040
I was out of breath, but God Almighty gives a person strength

31
00:01:57,239 --> 00:01:59,079
Great and powerful strength

32
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:04,599
He kept dragging me by my beard, saying, I’ll teach the whole town a lesson through you

33
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:10,159
He said to me, plainly, “The time of the Prophet is gone”

34
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:12,520
I told him, Are we now living in Pharaoh’s time?

35
00:02:13,199 --> 00:02:15,360
For you to say the Prophet’s era has passed?

36
00:02:15,919 --> 00:02:20,800
He dragged me by my beard until he brought me to the feet of Ibrahim al-Fakkash

37
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:22,680
Who was nicknamed al-Bariwi

38
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:24,560
He was sentenced along with me too

39
00:02:24,879 --> 00:02:29,159
They told us we’d been sentenced to execution, but the ruling hadn’t been carried out yet

40
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:32,319
He dragged me by my beard, pulling me along the ground

41
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:36,479
Until we reached the feet of Ibrahim al-Fakkash, nicknamed al-Bariwi

42
00:02:36,919 --> 00:02:38,360
He asked him, Do you know this man?

43
00:02:38,479 --> 00:02:39,560
He replied, Yes, I know him

44
00:02:39,599 --> 00:02:42,639
Abu Seif said to al-Bariwi, This is the clever player, al-Shuweimi

45
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:46,520
They called me the clever player because they never caught me with cigarettes

46
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:52,639
I’d been in so many prisons and detentions,arrested 27 times before by the Hisba (religious police)

47
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:57,080
Once they detained me for security reasons, and another time I spent a month and a half in Point 11

48
00:02:58,039 --> 00:03:00,120
That’s why they gave me that nickname

49
00:03:00,719 --> 00:03:05,439
He dragged me by my beard all that distance, pulled me out of the room again, still dragging me

50
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:14,400
I stayed with them in the investigation section for about 53 or 54 days

51
00:03:15,879 --> 00:03:16,879
They came

52
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:20,039
And shackled my hands behind my back again

53
00:03:21,159 --> 00:03:23,560
They took me out after 53 days

54
00:03:23,759 --> 00:03:24,759
And said to me

55
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:29,159
We’ll spare your neck if you pay a sum of money

56
00:03:30,719 --> 00:03:32,719
In exchange for paying a financial amount

57
00:03:33,159 --> 00:03:38,159
The ruling would be treated like theft but under a religious ruling

58
00:03:38,759 --> 00:03:41,680
In the past, people would say things like, I’ll rob you right before your eyes

59
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:43,879
My strength and my dignity

60
00:03:44,319 --> 00:03:47,560
They wanted to rob me, but in the name of what the Prophet said,meaning freeing a slave

61
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:52,039
They asked me, What property do you have? At that time, I owned 6 or 7 cars

62
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:56,360
Because I worked hard in the cigarette trade

63
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:59,960
Whether that work was forbidden or not

64
00:04:00,439 --> 00:04:03,000
Some people said it was forbidden, others said it wasn’t

65
00:04:03,039 --> 00:04:08,000
Maybe we were ignorant about it, but we didn’t really know whether it was forbidden or not

66
00:04:08,039 --> 00:04:11,000
The important thing is, I worked hard, forbidden or not

67
00:04:11,159 --> 00:04:13,479
I struggled and earned that money

68
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:19,360
They took everything I had,gold, silver, and cars

69
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:21,839
They took everything, even my farmland

70
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:24,360
I had a deed of ownership from 50 years ago

71
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,720
In my name, inherited from my father

72
00:04:26,759 --> 00:04:31,000
Back then, the Syrian regime used to seize land from people who owned a lot of it

73
00:04:31,519 --> 00:04:35,160
Out of fear, my father registered the land in his sons’ names

74
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:38,879
He divided the land equally among his sons

75
00:04:39,879 --> 00:04:41,959
So my share was the same as my brothers’

76
00:04:42,959 --> 00:04:45,639
Even the land that was originally my father’s

77
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:47,920
They made me fingerprint it as sold and bought

78
00:04:47,959 --> 00:04:50,879
I also had a motorbike with two frames at times

79
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:55,639
I used it around the neighborhood and inside the city during traffic jams and hot weather

80
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:58,399
They made me fingerprint that as sold and bought too
